{"parse":{"title":"Potato riots","pageid":12439007,"revid":834322018,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Vosstanile_krestian.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/35/Vosstanile_krestian.jpg/250px-Vosstanile_krestian.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"153\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/35/Vosstanile_krestian.jpg/375px-Vosstanile_krestian.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/35/Vosstanile_krestian.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"430\" data-file-height=\"264\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Vosstanile_krestian.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Peasant uprising of 1860 as depicted by <a href=\"/wiki/Sergei_Vasilyevich_Gerasimov\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sergei Vasilyevich Gerasimov\">Sergei Vasilyevich Gerasimov</a> (1951)</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>\"potato riots\"</b> were the mass anti-<a href=\"/wiki/Serfdom\" title=\"Serfdom\">serfdom</a> movement of <i>udelnye krestyane</i> (imperial <a href=\"/wiki/Peasant\" title=\"Peasant\">peasants</a>; peasants in the personal property lands of the Russian imperial house) in 1834, and of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=State_peasants&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"State peasants (page does not exist)\">state peasants</a> in 1840\u201344, in <a href=\"/wiki/Russian_Empire\" title=\"Russian Empire\">Russian Empire</a>. The reason for the rebellion was the coercive introduction  of <a href=\"/wiki/Potato\" title=\"Potato\">potato</a> cultivation. The government selected the best fertile sections for potatoes from peasant lands. Authorities enforced brutal punishments for the non-fulfillment of the orders and assessed different requisitions. In 1834 unrest flared up in <a href=\"/wiki/Kirov_Oblast\" title=\"Kirov Oblast\">Vyatsky</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Vladimir_Oblast\" title=\"Vladimir Oblast\">Vladimir</a> provinces, but it reached its height among the state peasants in 1840\u201344. Riots appeared simultaneously and they were partly in response to <a href=\"/wiki/Pavel_Kiselyov\" title=\"Pavel Kiselyov\">Pavel Kiselyov</a>'s reforms of state villages (1837\u201341). In the provinces of <a href=\"/wiki/Ural_(region)\" title=\"Ural (region)\">Ural</a> and the lower <a href=\"/wiki/Volga_Region\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Volga Region\">Volga Region</a> more than 500,000 peasants rose up destroying sowings of potatoes, and thrashing officials. They arbitrarily re-elected wardens, and attacked punitive detachments with weapons. Aside from ethnic Russians, participants in the riots included the <a href=\"/wiki/Mari_people\" title=\"Mari people\">Mari</a> population, <a href=\"/wiki/Chuvash_people\" title=\"Chuvash people\">Chuvashes</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Udmurt_people\" title=\"Udmurt people\">Udmurts</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Tatars\" title=\"Tatars\">Tatars</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Komi_people\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Komi people\">Komi</a>. The government sent troops to suppress the riots. In a number of places, peasants were shot. Thousands of rebels were convicted, and exiled into <a href=\"/wiki/Siberia\" title=\"Siberia\">Siberia</a> or forcibly drafted as soldiers.\n</p><p>The eschatological rumours associating potato planting with the service to the Antichrist has also contributed to the magnitude of the disturbances.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Potato_riots&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_food_riots\" title=\"List of food riots\">List of food riots</a></li></ul>\n<div class=\"noprint metadata navbox\" role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Portals\" style=\"font-weight:bold;padding:0.4em 2em\"><ul style=\"margin:0.1em 0 0\"><li style=\"display:inline\"><span style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\"><span style=\"margin:0 0.5em\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_Russia.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Flag of Russia.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f3/Flag_of_Russia.svg/24px-Flag_of_Russia.svg.png\" width=\"24\" height=\"16\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f3/Flag_of_Russia.svg/36px-Flag_of_Russia.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f3/Flag_of_Russia.svg/48px-Flag_of_Russia.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"900\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></span><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Russia\" title=\"Portal:Russia\">Russia portal</a></span></li><li style=\"display:inline\"><span style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\"><span style=\"margin:0 0.5em\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Logo_sociology.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Logo sociology.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Logo_sociology.svg/21px-Logo_sociology.svg.png\" width=\"21\" height=\"21\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Logo_sociology.svg/32px-Logo_sociology.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Logo_sociology.svg/42px-Logo_sociology.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"616\" data-file-height=\"616\" /></a></span><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Sociology\" title=\"Portal:Sociology\">Sociology portal</a></span></li><li style=\"display:inline\"><span style=\"display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap\"><span style=\"margin:0 0.5em\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:P_history.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"P history.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/P_history.svg/23px-P_history.svg.png\" width=\"23\" height=\"21\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/P_history.svg/